{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Kocak et al. [75] demonstrated that MK also improves resistance to carbonation and chloride penetration, protecting steel reinforcement from corrosion.",
    "Ngu et al. [77] observed that a 10% replacement level enhances sulfate resistance and reduces water absorption, further reducing permeability and increasing resistance to sulfate attack.",
    "Tambichik et al. [78] reported that POFA improves overall durability over time due to its pozzolanic reactions.",
    "Shafigh et al. [83] found that POFA reduces water absorption by 10-15% and increases resistance to chloride ion penetration, protecting against chloride-induced corrosion.",
    "Additional studies support POFA's effectiveness in harsh conditions, with Sumesh et al. [80] noting a 15-20% increase in sulfate resistance and reduced carbonation rates."
  ],
